sge-node-selection(1)                                    sge-node-selection(1)



NNAAMMEE
       busy-nodes,  idle-nodes,  dead-nodes, nodes-in-job, qselect-node-list -
       List Grid Engine node names by various criteria

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       bbuussyy--nnooddeess [--ww] [--hh|----hheellpp]
       iiddllee--nnooddeess [--ww] [--hh|----hheellpp]
       ddeeaadd--nnooddeess [--ww] [--hh|----hheellpp]
       nnooddeess--iinn--jjoobb [--ww] [--hh|----hheellpp] _j_o_b_i_d
       qqsseelleecctt--nnooddee--lliisstt [--hh|----hheellpp] _q_s_e_l_e_c_t___a_r_g ...

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       bbuussyy--nnooddeess, iiddllee--nnooddeess, and ddeeaadd--nnooddeess respectively  list  Grid  Engine
       nodes  which are:  busy with one or more jobs, idle (without a job run-
       ning), and "dead" (their Grid Engine exec daemon  is  not  responding).
       nnooddeess--iinn--jjoobb list nodes which are running the given _j_o_b_i_d (presumably a
       parallel one).  qqsseelleecctt--nnooddee--lliisstt runs _q_s_e_l_e_c_t(1) with the given  argu-
       ments.  The node list is printed one node per line unless the --ww option
       is used.

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       --hh,----hheellpp
              Print usage information.

       --ww     Print the output in a form compatible with the  --ww  argument  of
              _p_d_s_h(1).

EEXXAAMMPPLLEESS
       The  following would reboot all idle nodes.  (It is actually preferable
       to submit a job to reboot nodes, to avoid a race with job further  sub-
       mission.)
              ppddsshh --ww ``iiddllee--nnooddeess --ww`` rreebboooott

       The  following  would  run _q_h_o_s_t(1), selecting only nodes in job number
       "123".
              qqhhoosstt ``nnooddeess--iinn--jjoobb 112233``

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
       _q_h_o_s_t(1), _q_s_e_l_e_c_t(1), _p_d_s_h(1).

AAUUTTHHOORR
       Dave Love <d.love@liverpool.ac.uk>



